  "prompt": "Can someone screenshot a snap after I block them?",
  "response": "No, if you block someone on Snapchat, they won\u2019t be able to view your snaps, story, or chat with you. If they had already taken a screenshot of a snap before you blocked them, they would still have that screenshot. However, after you block them, they cannot access any new snaps or content you send.\n\nSnapchat typically notifies you if someone takes a screenshot of your snap, but this would only apply if the screenshot was taken before you blocked them. Always be cautious about what you share, as once someone has taken a screenshot, you lose control over that content.",
